    <h2 class="post">
            <div class="gravatar"><a href="https://connect.sensiolabs.com/api/alternates/17170f22-52c0-4adf-a75d-29cb01d53176"><img width="57" height="57" src="https://connect.sensiolabs.com/api/images/17170f22-52c0-4adf-a75d-29cb01d53176.png?format=57x57" alt="Javier Eguiluz"></a></div>
        <a href="/blog/a-week-of-symfony-290-16-22-july-2012">A week of symfony #290 (16-&gt;22 July 2012)</a>
        <div class="complementaries_informations">
    by
            <a href="https://connect.sensiolabs.com/api/alternates/17170f22-52c0-4adf-a75d-29cb01d53176">Javier Eguiluz</a>
            – July 23, 2012
        </div>
    </h2>

    <p>
        
This week, the Form component continued focusing all the Symfony2 development activity. Besides some tweaks and refactorings, most of the commits were related to form performance improvement. In addition, the official code repository achieved another remarkable milestone: more than <a href="http://github.com/symfony/symfony/pull/5000">5,000 pull requests</a> received.
    </p>
</div>
            
    <div class="box_hr"><hr /></div>


<div class="box_article">
    <div class="tag">
                    <a href="/blog/category/a-week-of-symfony">
                <strong>
                    A WEEK OF SYMFONY
                </strong>
            </a>
            </div>

    <h2 class="post">
            <div class="gravatar"><a href="https://connect.sensiolabs.com/api/alternates/17170f22-52c0-4adf-a75d-29cb01d53176"><img width="57" height="57" src="https://connect.sensiolabs.com/api/images/17170f22-52c0-4adf-a75d-29cb01d53176.png?format=57x57" alt="Javier Eguiluz"></a></div>
        <a href="/blog/a-week-of-symfony-289-9-15-july-2012">A week of symfony #289 (9-&gt;15 July 2012)</a>
        <div class="complementaries_informations">
    by
            <a href="https://connect.sensiolabs.com/api/alternates/17170f22-52c0-4adf-a75d-29cb01d53176">Javier Eguiluz</a>
            – July 23, 2012
        </div>
    </h2>

    <p>
        
This week Symfony project experienced the most intense development activity in years. In addition to the three new versions released (<a href="http://symfony.com/blog/symfony-2-0-16-released">2.0.16</a>, <a href="http://symfony.com/blog/symfony-2-1-0-beta2-released">2.1.0 beta2</a>, and <a href="http://symfony.com/blog/symfony-2-1-0-beta3-released">2.1.0 beta3</a>), a major cleanup of tickets and pull requests was made on the official repository. Particularly noteworthy was the refactoring of the form component and its huge performance boost.
    </p>
</div>
            
    <div class="box_hr"><hr /></div>


